Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.83,0:00:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}OK, everypony, as you know,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.06,0:00:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the adorable fairy\Ncreatures known as Breezies
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.85,0:00:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,are about to come\Nthrough Ponyville.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.95,0:00:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! It's so exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.03,0:00:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait for Rainbow Dash\Nto make the breeze for them
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.94,0:00:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,so I can see how cute\Nthey are up close!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.56,0:00:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never done it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.35,0:00:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that I won't be\Ntotally awesome at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.24,0:00:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I totally will.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.95,0:00:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And that breeze\Nis very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But so is cheering on those\Nteeny, tiny little things
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.96,0:00:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so they have the confidence\Nto ride that breeze
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.00,0:00:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to their native land.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.52,0:00:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I mention how tiny they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.46,0:00:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So tiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.79,0:00:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking we could do\Na special Breezy cheer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.32,0:00:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I LOVE CHEERS!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.80,0:00:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But these cheers\Nshould be quiet cheers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.60,0:00:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to\Nstartle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They need to be\Nable to concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.25,0:00:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we try it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.13,0:00:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Breezies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.22,0:00:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,YOU CAN DO IT, BREEZIES!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.40,0:00:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.89,0:01:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Fluttershy, I had\Nno idea how hard it was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to do a cheer quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.25,0:01:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's OK. Quiet doesn't come\Nnaturally for everypony.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.70,0:01:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.23,0:01:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,YOU CAN DO IT, BREEZIES!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.08,0:01:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps just a\Nlittle bit quieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.91,0:01:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Breezies!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.71,0:01:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little quieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.37,0:01:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Breezies!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.15,0:01:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,PERFECT!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.95,0:01:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, um, I mean...yay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.72,0:01:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by YayPonies\Nhttp://yayponies.eu
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.76,0:02:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's too strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.09,0:02:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gotta slow\Nthis breeze down
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.94,0:02:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or we're going to blow\Nthose Breezies apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.67,0:02:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What I don't understand is\Nwhy they need the Pegasi
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.20,0:02:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a breeze for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.83,0:02:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see,\Nit's the breeze
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.02,0:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that activates the\NBreezie's magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.26,0:02:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And that magic protects the\Npollen they're carrying
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.60,0:02:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from being destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.27,0:02:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So no breeze means no magic\Nmeans the pollen goes bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.01,0:02:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.93,0:02:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And they only have two days\Nto get that pollen back
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.68,0:02:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,before the portal to\Ntheir home closes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's\Never so important
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.22,0:02:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that we help them make their\Nway through Ponyville safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.45,0:03:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We certainly wouldn't\Nwant to scare them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.22,0:03:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and divert them from their path!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.30,0:03:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.38,0:03:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You certainly know\Na lot about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.73,0:03:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.14,0:03:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to see them\Ngathering their pollen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.75,0:03:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in Western Equestria.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.35,0:03:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Rarity, I hate\Nto weigh in with you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to fashion, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.88,0:03:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There's too much\Npurple on this, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.97,0:03:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I KNEW it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.68,0:03:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But Twilight\Nrefused to admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What? I--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NIt's the perfect amount of purple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.89,0:03:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that there's an awful\Nlot of sequins on your jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.79,0:03:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, darling, please! One can\Nnever have too many sequins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.94,0:03:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can if they\Nreflect the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the light catches a group of\NBreezies right in their eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.07,0:03:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and blinds them long enough to\Nget them off their course
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.92,0:03:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so they never get home!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.96,0:03:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I stand corrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.14,0:03:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose there is\Nthe rare instance
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.94,0:03:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,where one can have\Ntoo many sequins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.84,0:03:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just take\Noff my jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:04:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose this won't do either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.19,0:04:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony, it's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.41,0:04:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Please welcome the Breezies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.54,0:04:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're as cute as Apple\NBloom on the day she was born!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.90,0:04:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And would you look at those\Nadorable little packs
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.38,0:04:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they carry their pollen in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.25,0:04:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So! Cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.98,0:04:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't! Take! It!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinkie Pie! Can I hop on you\Nso I can see the Breezies?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.48,0:04:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,May! Explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,OH NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.69,0:05:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Slow down the breeze for\Nthe other group to catch up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.39,0:05:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're too far back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't connect the breeze\Nto both sets of Breezies!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.82,0:05:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we speed it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the first group\Nwill be going too fast
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.78,0:05:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and will get separated\Nfrom each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.50,0:06:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Manglemarsh mooth!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.10,0:06:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.06,0:06:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You must all gather as\Nclose as you possibly can!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.86,0:06:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Muggledy Sarken dose?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I understand the language\Nof all kinds of creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be so proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.50,0:06:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And you speak my language, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.63,0:06:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I can. This lot can\Nonly understand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.72,0:06:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, they're not the\Nbrightest bunch around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,THAT...WAS...AMAZING!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry we couldn't\Nget a breeze going
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that would get them\Nback to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.96,0:06:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.52,0:06:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I for one am very proud\Nof you, Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaping into action\Nlike that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.83,0:06:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I should design\Nyou a special hero's gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.76,0:07:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a sash. At least a sash.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.60,0:07:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}OK, OK, OK!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.99,0:07:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you're all thinking.\NWhy don't you just say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.62,0:07:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.31,0:07:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is all my fault!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.98,0:07:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so, so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.70,0:07:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Spike, it's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.00,0:07:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have happened\Nto any one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.57,0:07:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.29,0:07:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I'm just going to\Nstay over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So Fluttershy, you want us to\Nget the breeze going again
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.35,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so these little guys\Ncan get a move on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.40,0:07:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should wait\Njust a moment or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.05,0:07:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been through so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.30,0:07:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just give me the word when\Nyou think they're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Twirly, you look\Nlike you need a blanket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.60,0:08:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sampkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.74,0:08:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.98,0:08:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Melanky?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.29,0:08:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Did you need\Nsome more water?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.12,0:08:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now who else needed a\Nhoof-knitted sweater?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.91,0:08:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.90,0:08:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.55,0:08:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But watch your step.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.69,0:08:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops. Sorry about\Nthat little one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.96,0:08:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to see if you\Nthought the Breezies were ready
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.99,0:08:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to give it another try.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.55,0:08:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Has it been an hour already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.14,0:08:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.43,0:08:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Time flies when you're making\Nsure little creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,don't feel that you're\Nabandoning them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.90,0:08:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to the cruel world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.83,0:08:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're not going\Nto a cruel world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.20,0:08:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes! That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,On second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.17,0:08:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think\Nthey're quite ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.86,0:09:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Marshkin pupskin larfer!\NFarclop pannywafer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.20,0:09:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, what did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.52,0:09:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather not say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.33,0:09:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, well, I'm sure you\Nknow what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.45,0:09:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No one knows rare magical\Ncreatures like you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.39,0:09:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just wait for your word.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.76,0:09:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.72,0:09:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be in touch very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.58,0:09:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to go NOW or\Nwe will never get home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.86,0:09:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we did not need\Nthat stupid breeze
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to activate our magic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.67,0:09:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or I would just force you\Nall to fly home right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.13,0:09:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we have to need magic\Nto keep our pollen safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Seabreeze--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.71,0:09:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you giving\Nin to these wimps?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.88,0:09:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If they had not been so\Nscared in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,this never would have happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that is just\Nnot true, Seabreeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.41,0:09:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because of a\Nleaf and you know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.02,0:09:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.43,0:09:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no idea what\Nthey're doing out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.43,0:09:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you said, we need as\Nmuch time as we can get,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.82,0:10:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are so incompetent!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.27,0:10:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I didn't say that\Nexactly, now did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.19,0:10:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, maybe a snack\Nwill lighten the mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.90,0:10:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Munfarzen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.95,0:10:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're excused.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.65,0:10:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my Breezies? I\Nthink we can all agree
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.56,0:10:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that now that you've eaten and\Nyou have a little energy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.78,0:10:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,going in your Breezy bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.47,0:10:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you're strong enough\Nto face the breeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.41,0:10:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've loved having you here and\NI hope I've made you all feel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.26,0:10:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,loved and special.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.62,0:10:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to go; no\Npony here will deny that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.78,0:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There is nothing special{\i0}\N{\i1}about these losers!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They cannot handle a\Nsimple breeze home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.32,0:10:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If they could just stick with\Nthe program and listen to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.04,0:10:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we would be safe! AT HOME!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.25,0:10:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Home! Where everybreezie\Nis like us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.97,0:11:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A confusing pep talk,\Nbut nonetheless,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.25,0:11:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I do know that if you\Ndon't leave soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.23,0:11:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you may never make it back\Nand that would be terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.20,0:11:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.34,0:11:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Multy marshkin follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.93,0:11:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,MULTY marskin toomba too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.57,0:11:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea you\Nall have colds!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.06,0:11:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? All of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.32,0:11:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear. I can't let you\Ngo out there sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.43,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of a friend would\NI be if I made you go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.91,0:11:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wondering if the\NBreezies are ready to go yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.23,0:12:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Clock's kind of ticking\Nfor them to make it back
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.05,0:12:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,before the door\Ncloses on their home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes. I mean, not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, maybe just a\Nfew more minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.17,0:12:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.98,0:12:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We wait too much longer,\Nwe'll have to create
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.89,0:12:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,such a strong breeze it may\Nbe more than they can handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.50,0:12:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to\Ntrust Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.67,0:12:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,She must know what\Nshe's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.89,0:12:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Awwww!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.55,0:12:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you spending\Nyour time on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.98,0:12:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never get home!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.27,0:12:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Breezies, I must say,\NSeabreeze has a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.32,0:12:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's time for me to get\NRainbow Dash and her friends
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.59,0:12:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can create the breeze\Nfor you to get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.36,0:12:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. You're all awfully anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you\Nto feel abandoned
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.99,0:13:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or that I wasn't the most kind\Nhost I could possibly be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.03,0:13:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Doshin bafin dorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.71,0:13:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that does make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.27,0:13:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Seabreeze, do you\Nthink you could wait
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.84,0:13:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}just a couple more hours?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.45,0:13:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Seabreeze? Seabreeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.55,0:13:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Has anypony seen Seabreeze?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.14,0:13:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way he can handle\Nbeing out there on his own!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.86,0:14:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Excuse me, bees?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.66,0:14:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you please back\Noff my Breezy friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.74,0:14:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't mean any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.91,0:14:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.79,0:14:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working on a bee type dance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.55,0:14:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and was hoping you{\i0}\N{\i1}could help me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.11,0:14:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Does this bring to mind{\i0}\N{\i1}any images for you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.57,0:14:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps a bee?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.30,0:14:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Excuse me!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.87,0:14:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have done NOTHING but be kind,\Nbut I guess that is NOT working!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You bees know better than\Nto hurt a helpless Breezie!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.22,0:14:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I demand that you go away NOW\Nor you'll have to answer to ME!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.07,0:15:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankylin!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.22,0:15:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.48,0:15:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.79,0:15:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Of course!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.22,0:15:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You could have gotten\Nseriously hurt out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.17,0:15:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ponyville is much too\Ndangerous for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.50,0:15:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One tiny acorn is a threat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.87,0:15:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.32,0:15:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That is one reason why
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.99,0:15:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been trying to get us\Nto go from the beginning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.48,0:15:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.13,0:15:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just trying not to\Nhurt any creature's feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.42,0:15:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,my displays of kindness\Nmay have cost you everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.01,0:15:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is running out and\Nyou may never make it home!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.35,0:15:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That is exactly what I have\Nbeen telling all of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.34,0:15:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but they do not listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.42,0:15:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No Breezie\Never listens to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.54,0:15:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Seabreeze, I understand\Nyour feelings are hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.02,0:15:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's hard for them to hear\Nyou when you're shouting
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.32,0:15:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and being mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The message doesn't get across.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.05,0:15:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about those bees?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.39,0:15:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were not nice to them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.72,0:16:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was the only\Nway they listened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but they HAD to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.51,0:16:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And they wouldn't listen\Nto me any other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.16,0:16:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to go. Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My dear Breezies,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to rescue Seabreeze\Nfrom serious harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.79,0:16:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I know more than\Never that you must leave
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.12,0:16:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,before it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You would never\Nsurvive in Ponyville.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mulshy barfin gorfis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.88,0:16:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help you anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.93,0:16:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I wasn't helping\Nyou at all by being nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.31,0:16:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But the truth of the matter\Nis that I must be firm!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.59,0:16:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You must go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.27,0:16:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,NOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.80,0:17:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.07,0:17:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do it any lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.85,0:17:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither can I!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.72,0:17:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly back! I'm going to try and\Nsee if I can slow it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's too light!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.12,0:17:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This will never get them home!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my. Maybe it's because\Nthere are too few of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.80,0:17:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When they started their\Njourney there was more of them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.70,0:17:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to face the breeze together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been studying\Nan old spell book
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.08,0:17:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Castle of\Nthe Two Sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.09,0:17:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a spell that\NI think could help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.49,0:17:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is probably going to\Nfeel a little funny at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.05,0:17:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're going to\Nhave to trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.64,0:17:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I love new ideas that make\Nme feel funny at first!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.37,0:18:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.37,0:18:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Marful fly bartontook.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.52,0:18:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I mean, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.81,0:18:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Marshkin parskin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.23,0:18:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.45,0:18:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.11,0:19:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sorry for how I\Ntreated you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.70,0:19:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not right that\NI called you names.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.00,0:19:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not even really believe\Nthose things I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.57,0:19:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was worried we would never\Nget back to our home,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.46,0:19:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and I lashed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.91,0:19:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.93,0:19:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold onto me, let us\Njoin the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.14,0:19:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy mini-sized paradise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.84,0:19:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is simply beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.16,0:19:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So much inspiration!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.73,0:19:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is my sketch\Npad when I need it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.84,0:19:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,SO! STINKIN'! CUTE!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.36,0:20:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You OK, Fluttershy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.91,0:20:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just so very happy they\Ngot to be reunited
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with their family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.09,0:20:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd better get going\Nbefore the entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.04,0:20:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}well, exit for us, closes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.19,0:20:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Breezies.\NI must go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.48,0:20:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To remember us by.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.85,0:20:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.01,0:20:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll miss you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.86,0:20:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll miss all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.63,0:20:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My experiences with{\i0}\N{\i1}the Breezies{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}have helped me to see that{\i0}\N{\i1}kindness can take many forms.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.48,0:20:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And sometimes being too kind{\i0}\N{\i1}can actually keep a friend{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.54,0:20:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from doing what they need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pushing them away{\i0}\N{\i1}may seem cruel,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.95,0:20:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but it's sometimes the{\i0}\N{\i1}kindest thing you can do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.56,0:21:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa. That was a close one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.32,0:21:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, gather around!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.99,0:21:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh, I've always kind of\Nwondered what it would be like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.56,0:21:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a Gryphon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.16,0:21:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.35,0:21:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure? What about a\Ndragon? No?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.69,0:21:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to shoot fire!
